It is the 15th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}, preceded by {{ill|Teiushi|ja|дЄБдЄС}} and followed by {{ill|Kib≈Н|ja|еЈ±еНѓ}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°М}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤}} symbol {{ill|Bo|ja|жИК|1=Tsuchinoe (жИК)}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|еЬЯ}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|еНБдЇМжФѓ}} symbol {{ill|Tiger|ja|еѓЕ|1=Tiger (zodiac)|lt=Tiger (еѓЕ)}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|жЬ®}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|дЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥#зЫЄеЙЛпЉИгБЭгБЖгБУгБПпЉЙ|lt=Mutual Restraint|lt_ja=зЫЄеЙЛ}}) (Wood overcomes Earth).

