In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|и•њжЪ¶|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} year whose final digit is 0 or 5 (when the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еНБеє≤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} are {{ill|K≈Н|ja|еЇЪ|1=Kanoe (еЇЪ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Etsu|ja|дєЩ|1=Kinoto (дєЩ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}), the month of {{ill|January|ja|1жЬИ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} is designated as the Bointora {{ill|month (calendar)|ja|жЬИ (жЪ¶)|lt=Month|lt_ja=жЬИ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|жЧІжЪ¶|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Beginning of Spring|ja|зЂЛжШ•|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} until the day before {{ill|Jingzhe|lt=Awakening of Insects|ja|еХУиЯД|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) as applicable.

